    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-18T07:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-18T07:29:00-05:00" n="964"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/272</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Archangel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-18T17:00:00+04:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 2, 12.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. My telegrams Nos. 110, 111 contain text of the proclamation to the Finns of
                    all countries which I have obtained from Senator <pb facs="0895" n="805"
                        xml:id="pg_805"/>
                    <persName>Tokoi</persName>, former head of the Finnish Red Labor Government, and
                    which I am forwarding with the approval of the Ambassador.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d964fn1">Not printed.</note> The above-mentioned Finn is the same
                    man for whom our Ambassador recently forwarded a proclamation to be inserted in
                    the Stockholm Finnish newspaper.<note n="2" xml:id="d964fn2">See the
                        Ambassador’s telegram No. 362 of Aug. 13, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_803">p. 803</ref>.</note> Actual Finnish text will also be
                    sent to be inserted in the following Finnish newspapers should you deem it
                    advisable: <hi rend="italic">Riavaaja</hi>, Fitchburg, Massachusetts; (2) <hi
                        rend="italic">Tyomiennui</hi> of Calumet, Michigan; (3) <hi rend="italic"
                        >Tyokansa</hi> at Port Arthur, Canada; (4) <hi rend="italic">Toveri</hi>
                    printed in Astoria, Oregon State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
